<a href="javascript:card_browser(125)">Ulaire Enquea, Lieutenant of Morgul</a> x2     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> UPDATE 1:  "Worlds"- The Withcking is the Twilight Witchking. <br>
also drop one naz sword for a Black steed.<br>
<br>
END UPDATE<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
This is the same fellowship with two additional cards as Watching the Gong Show waiting for Zorro.  I have two different shadow decks this is my secondary.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Again Sting is very important.  I use 3 so I can get it out quickly.  Look at opponents hand every fellowship phase and if you forget whats there use it during the regroup phase.  Make sure to look at every card in the hand.  Free Peeps, Shadow, weapons, events etc.  For more look at the previous deck listed above.<br>
<br>
<br>
The fellowship is pretty simple.  bid between 5-8 depending on meta and opponent.  go first.  pull sam remove three and hope he lives to remove the rest.  Move 1-2 stop. hope opponent moves to three but dont worry to much if he doesnt.  With any luck youll be playing another nazgul deck.  then just move as you deem neccessary.  You have as much as 8 servants with barliman and fireworks or up to 6 sleeps.  With this shadow drawing is not as important but it is their if you need it.   Your deck does well against every shadow deck.  For Nazgul you have 2 flaming brands armor and servants.  For moria you have sleep.  for sauron you have sleep.  for Uruks armor and the servants should get the job done.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Shadow is a little more complicated.  The twilight are there for the extra wounds they give.  So less gets healed at a sanctuary.  the main thing is to get 4 burdens and Toldea actvve.  then with drawn to its power you can assign toldea to whoever you can beat and do it again when he is fierce they die and you add x burdens where x is the number of Drawn to its Power you have out.  Black Breaths but no blade tips?  Its simple not enough room for both and I would rather keep the wounds that I do deal on than put on wounds that get healed away.  thE swords are for xtra power and damage.  Power in Terror gets rid of pesky allies and the freaking Mirror which has now replaced Thror&#39;s Map as the cheesiest card in the game.  It always was pretty bad though.  Thats about it.  If you dont corrupt them hopefully you will have at least slowed them down.  Oh yeah the 4 Canteas are in there to get rid of flaming brands.  Good Luck<br>
<br>
